@toc main
@node main "OCHMANN ILLUMINATIO MEA"

   @{"DigiOchmann or Ochmannumérique" system "sys:utilities/multiview illuminatio.ilbm"} v0.9 (released April 2001) is a versatile and user friendly vocabulary driller. It can be used in a wide variety of language learning situations and it encourages vocabulary development with its easy-to-use and pleasant interface. 

   @{" Features                  " link features}
   @{" Requirements              " link req}
   @{" Installation              " link install}

   @{" How to use                " link howto}

   @{" Licence and release notes " link relnotes}
@endnode
@node features "Features"

   @{b}Features@{ub}
   * An easy to use interface with customisable colours
   * Fully localised for English and French. Own locale easy to make.
   * Support for languages using Latin1 and AmigaPL
   * Unlimited vocabulary lists with smart organisation of folders and cells
   * System-friendly and 100% AMOS free

   @{b}To Do@{ub}
   This version of @{b}DIGIOchmann@{ub} does not yet:
   * support sound
   * have full error support
@endnode
@node req "Requirements"

   @{b}DIGIOchmann@{ub} requires

   * AmigaOS 3.0 or better
   * the AGA chipset
   * a VGA monitor is recommended but not required

   The programme has not been tested with any graphic cards. If you do and succeed or fail, please @{"let us know" link relnotes}.
@endnode
@node install "Installation"

   @{b}To install@{ub} just use the supplied Installer script. 

   If you prefer to install manually, be aware of the following:

   * The programme will refuse to work if it cannot find all the fonts supplied.
   * DIGIOchmann requires a separate directory with an OCHMANN: assign, where all the locale files (#?.digilang) and cells should live.
@endnode
@node howto "Usage"

   We think DIGIOchmann is so simple to use it should not take you more than 5 minutes to figure out how to use it. If you experience any problems, here are some notes.

   @{b}Structure@{ub}
   Vocabulary lists in @{b}DIGIOchmann@{ub} are organised in @{u}files@{uu} and @{u}cells@{uu}. One file can contain many cells.
   On first running, @{b}DIGIOchmann@{ub} will create a default @{u}file@{uu} (named "file") where the cells will be stored. You can create, choose a different one and rename the current @{u}file@{uu} by clicking @{u}Extras@{uu} and an appropriate tab.

   @{b}Cells@{ub}
   To use the programme, you need to create a @{u}New Cell@{uu} and eventually a set of cells. You need to choose a name for each cell and will then be shown a parameters tab.
   * The @{u}test@{uu} setting chooses between an ordered testing of the entries of the list and a randomised practice. Choose a method that suites you more.
   * Large (more than 30 entries, say) cells can be difficult to learn. If you prefer to take tests and learn smaller portions of the list in one go, then choose the quantity in @{u}group@{uu}. Note that you will not be able to allow for groupping until the cell contains an approprate number of entries.
   * The practice part of the programme can ask you whether to accept and answer when it is mistyped - @{u} when wrong@{uu} (since you should know if you mistyped a word or whether you simply did not remember it). You can also be asked for confirmation at each answer (even if your answer is an exact match) with @{u}always@{uu} or never be asked for confirmation with @{u}never@{uu}.
   When you have chosen the options and clicked on @{u}proceed@{uu}, you will be taken to the editor screen.

   @{b}Editor@{ub}
   The editor is quite self-explanatory. The @{u}question@{uu} is what the practice screen displays and it awaits an answer as specified by you in the @{u}answer@{uu} field.
   When you have created some entries, you can leave the editor with @{u}Save & Go@{uu} or by pressing the @{u}ESC@{uu} key. @{u}Abandon & Go@{uu} will loose all the changes made while @{u}Remove entry@{uu} will remove the entry currently displayed in the question-answer panel. You can select an entry by clicking on it in the frame.

   @{b}Practice@{ub}
   With a new cell, you will be able to use the @{u}practice@{uu} part of the programme by selecting the cell you want to use and then clicking @{u}practice@{uu}. This part is even more inuitive and does not need any more documentation.
   When you have finished your go with the cell, your overall result will be displayed. If you have scored more than 75%, the practice will be regarded as a success and you will see that the @{u}last practiced@{uu} field has changed.
   You can also change the name, parameters or remove a cell at any point by selecting the approprioate tab at the main screen.

   @{b}Extra features@{ub}
   Each vocabulary @{u}file@{uu} can have additional properties unique to it: the locale and the display colours, both can be adjusted in the @{u}Prefereces@{uu} menu.

   An additional note regarding @{u}AmigaPl@{uu} encoded fonts: to be able to use this feature, you must enable it in the @{u}Preferences@{uu} which will make them available in the editor.

@endnode
